keeping it as isOPDumpsEnabled to avoid confusion with not allowed scenarios

Which component triggering the hardware dump? is it PDC (phosphor-debug-collector) or ODC (openpower-debug-collector)?

If ODC then, I guess this policy check should go there right?
dump policies can be handled in a common place ie PDC

Which component triggering the hardware dump? is it PDC (phosphor-debug-collector) or ODC (openpower-debug-collector)?

If ODC then, I guess this policy check should go there right?
PDC is handling policy for dumps which are not collected by ODC so keeping in a common place
is it only for system dump or for all host dumps?
all host dumps

JS: isOPDumpsPolicyEnabled?
Ack
Just a few suggestions from CPP coding perspective.
auto enabled = true; better, auto bEnabled = true; Just a suggestion
Done

enabled can be declared and initialized here only rather than doing it at line no 26. Advantage, the variable is less scoped thus less chance of missing it and also the purpose gets very clear since the beginning
It is used outside this scope

Can we use header guard instead of pragma once? Reason being, 1) pragma once isn't a standard one yet (although since GCC 3.4 it is supported) but if someday we plan to make OpenPower for any other compiler which doesn't support pragma then there might be a problem. 2) If the same header file is copied into two places then it considers the pragma as different and multiple inclusion might happen.
that is being used in otherfiles.. we may need a separate commit if we decided to change that
A line break here may make it a bit more nice looking :-)
